
Pimp My Search was a novelty website to create a Google lookalike webpage, replacing the word "Google" with a word or phrase of the user's choice. The site was closed down later in 2009, citing a dispute over 'trademark issues'.

==Controversies with Google==

In February 2009, Pimp my Search ended Google search facilities and a posted a message that read: "Because of Trademark issues Google is no longer allowing searches from us...".http://www.pimpmysearch.com/problem.php?q=  Retrieved on 2009-05-25. Currently, the site remains closed, with the following message displayed: "Because of Trademark issues Pimp my Search is closed for ever.http://www.pimpmysearch.com  Retrieved on 2009-05-25.

